{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":97075,"duration_api_ms":179386,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e8035316-2b7c-4fa5-9725-cb34a7b723c8","total_cost_usd":0.5289680500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":3983,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30173,"cache_read_input_tokens":79914,"output_tokens":3229,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30173,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":173,"outputTokens":12819,"cacheReadInputTokens":704568,"cacheCreationInputTokens":52052,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.19978979999999993,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3983,"outputTokens":3229,"cacheReadInputTokens":79914,"cacheCreationInputTokens":30173,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.32917825,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All five amendments are verified as real bugs through code inspection. Two amendments (fr-2-467b53d8 and fr-2-b5ae378d) describe the same cancellation-during-backoff bug from different angles — both valid. The BackendUnavailable→BinaryNotFound blanket mapping (fr-2-77935ca0) is confirmed as a semantic and retryability regression affecting auth, transport, and service-unavailability errors across multiple adapters. The process-group kill gap (fr-2-fa361db6) is confirmed: process_backend.rs only signals the direct child PID with no setsid/setpgid setup, while tmux.rs already demonstrates the correct pattern. The test assertion count mismatch (fr-2-b5e89a50) is confirmed across all four cited tests where stub failures were changed from 3 to 5 but assertions still expect 4 stage entries.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-2-467b53d8","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. engine.rs:4642-4655 passes the original `&error` (e.g. TransportFailure from the prior attempt) to `fail_run_result` when cancellation is detected during backoff sleep. The `failure_label()` function extracts `failure_class` from this error, producing \"transport_failure\". The test at workflow_engine_test.rs:3870 asserts `failure_class == \"cancellation\"` and will fail. The fix — constructing AppError::InvocationCancelled before calling fail_run_result — is correct and targeted."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-77935ca0","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. error.rs:302 blanket-maps every `AppError::BackendUnavailable` to `FailureClass::BinaryNotFound`, which has `RetryRule::terminal()` (max_attempts=1, retryable=false) in retry_policy.rs:57. Multiple adapters return BackendUnavailable for non-binary conditions: missing OPENROUTER_API_KEY (process_backend.rs), 401/403 HTTP errors (openrouter_backend.rs), and GitHub HTTP/JSON failures (github.rs). These are now all mislabeled as \"binary_not_found\" and made permanently non-retryable, which is a semantic and operational regression. The mapping must be restricted to actual binary-not-found paths (spawn failure, exit code 127)."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b5ae378d","decision":"accept","rationale":"This describes the same cancellation-during-backoff bug as fr-2-467b53d8 from a slightly different angle and is independently valid. The tokio::select! cancellation branch at engine.rs:4642 falls through to `fail_run_result(&error, ...)` with the prior backend error. The test expects \"cancellation\" but gets \"transport_failure\". Both amendments identify the same root cause and propose the same correct fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-fa361db6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. process_backend.rs:365 uses `signal::kill(Pid::from_raw(pid), signal)` targeting only the direct child PID. No `setsid`, `setpgid`, or `pre_exec` calls exist to establish a process group. The cancel path (line 1304 via send_sigterm) and timeout path (line 1022 via spawn_background_reap → send_sigkill) all use the same flawed send_signal. Meanwhile tmux.rs:992-993 correctly signals both the process group (`Pid::from_raw(-pid)`) and the direct PID. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex backends will survive SIGKILL as orphaned processes. The fix requires both process-group setup at spawn time and group-targeted signaling, following the existing tmux pattern."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b5e89a50","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified across all four cited locations. Each test configures `with_transient_failure(stage, 5)` but asserts `stage_entries.len() == 4`. With 5 transient failures and TransportFailure's default max_attempts=5, the stage is entered 5 times during the failed run, plus 1 more on resume = 6 total entries. The assertions expecting 4 are stale from when the stub was configured with 3 failures (3 entries in failed run + 1 on resume = 4). The fix is straightforward: update the expected counts to match the new retry budget."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"6e9c77ed-2b73-4bda-a17c-1571ee527b7a"}
